class Solution {
    public boolean hasAlternatingBits(int n) {
        while (n > 0) {
            int current = n % 2;
            int previous = n % 10;
            if (current == previous) {
                return false;
            }
            n /= 10;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through the binary representation of the number from right to left, checking if each bit is different from the previous one. It achieves high efficiency by using a constant amount of space and a time complexity that depends on the number of digits in the binary representation of the input number.

